<teaserTitle>Garden Salad</teaserTitle>
<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>What could be more refreshing than a crunchy Garden Salad with our home-made vinaigrette?</p><p><br/></p></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>What could be more refreshing than a crunchy Garden Salad with our home-made <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../../../Videos/Recipes/Our%203%20Favorite%20Vinaigrettes%20Video.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Videos/Recipes/Our%203%20Favorite%20Vinaigrettes%20Video">vinaigrette</a>? All you need is green salad leaves, tomatos, cucumbers, bellpeppers and onions. And it's <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../Magazine%20Spring/Story%201%20-%20A%20Perfect%20Picnic/A%20Per94b228e4.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Editorial/Content/Magazine%20Spring/Story%201%20-%20A%20Perfect%20Picnic/A%20Perfect%20Picnic%20Article">easy to prepare at a picnic.</a></p><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><p>For the vinaigrette:</p><ul><li>3 tablespoons fresh orange juice</li><li>1 1/2 tablespoons fresh lime juice</li><li>2 1/2 teaspoons extravirgin olive oil</li><li>2 teaspoons honey</li><li>1 teaspoon red wine vinegar</li><li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li><li>1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper</li></ul><p>For the salad:</p><ul><li>1 1/2 cups (1 x 1/4-inch) julienne-cut zucchini</li><li>1 1/2 cups (1 x 1/4-inch) julienne-cut yellow squash</li><li>1 cup fresh corn kernels (about 2 ears)</li><li>2 tablespoons finely chopped red onion</li><li>1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley</li><li>1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh basil</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><p>To prepare vinaigrette, combine the first 7 ingredients, stirring with a whisk.<br/>To prepare salad, combine zucchini and remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add vinaigrette; toss well. Cover and chill.</p><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>For more pleasure while cutting the vegetables, use our <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../../Products/Fall%20Campaign/Japanese%20Knife%20Product%20Teaser.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Editorial/Products/Fall%20Campaign/Japanese%20Knife%20Product%20Teaser">super sharp Japanese knives</a>, then <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../../Products/Fall%20Campaign/Pepper%20Mill%20Product%20Teaser.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Editorial/Products/Fall%20Campaign/Pepper%20Mill%20Product%20Teaser">grind some fresh pepper</a> and add your prepared <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../../../Videos/Recipes/Our%203%20Favorite%20Vinaigrettes%20Video.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Videos/Recipes/Our%203%20Favorite%20Vinaigrettes%20Video">vinaigrette.</a></p></div></detailText>
